Thailand Stocks: Bangkok First Investment, Khon Kaen, Thai Air

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-06-10T09:50:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/thailand-stocks-bfit-securities-khon-kaen-siam-city-cement.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 4:30 p.m. close in Bangkok.  The SET Index rose 3.52 points, or 0.4 percent, to
1,020.37, a second day of gains, paring a weekly decline of 3.5
percent.  BFIT Securities Pcl (BSEC)  , a Thai stock brokerage,
added 0.8 percent to 2.4 baht. OSK Investment Bank Bhd. received
approval from Malaysian regulators to acquire a 49 percent stake
in BFIT, the Thai company said in a regulatory filing.  Bangkok
First Investment & Trust Pcl (BFIT)  , the parent of BFIT
Securities, jumped 6.6 percent to 7.25 baht.  Khon Kaen Sugar Industry Pcl (KSL)  , a sugar miller,
climbed 3.7 percent to 14 baht, a one-week high. The company had
its share-price forecast raised to 15.4 baht from 15.2 baht at
KGI Securities (Thailand) Pcl, which said higher exports will
boost the company’s earnings.  Thai Airways International Pcl (THAI)  , the country’s
largest carrier, lost 2.5 percent to 29.75 baht, the lowest
close since July 8. The airline filled fewer seats in May than
in the previous month, it said in a statement today. The
carrier’s average cabin load factor was 62 percent, down from 72
percent in April, which was also the average for the first five
months of the year, the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at  
 dboey@bloomberg.net . 